The paper deals with the problem of sparsifying neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning and specifically in deep learning. The approach proposed involves regularization and pruning, which are techniques commonly used in optimization and model selection. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the performance of the method on various datasets, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
